    "notes": "CTA keeps B1 fixed in absolute meters while wing span can vary. B2 is defined as a fraction of wing span, with wing span = B2 + B3. C0/body chord, C3/transition-wing chord, transition taper ratio C4/C3, and C5/wing tip chord remain active. C1 is derived from fixed sweep S and straight TE(C0->C1). There is no public C2 parameter; the inboard TE blend from C1 to C3 uses a hidden helper point. Transition-wing sweep S1 is defined on the 50% chord line and outer-wing sweep S2 on the 25% chord line. TE(C3->C4) is no longer forced to stay straight. Twist stays constant from root to C3.",
